title: Syed Khurshid Ahmed Shah wins NA-201 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party (PPP) Parliamentarian Candidate Syed Khurshid Ahmed Shah has won the election for National Assembly constituency NA-201 Sukkur-II by securing 1,20,219 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by the Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Jamiat Ulema-e-Islam candidate Mohammad Saleh Indhar, who bagged 53,302 votes.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 50.44 percent.
